The Tory, 48, had announced his intention to resign on April 14, but did not complete the formalities until last week - meaning he received his full taxpayer-funded salary for last month. Khan, who won the "RedWall" seat of Wakefield, West Yorks, from Labour in 2019, was found guilty at Southwark Crown Court last month of sexually assaulting a 15-year-old in 2008. He is appealing against his conviction.